SUMMARY:🌳☕ ST. CLAIR WEST VILLAGE WALK\, WYCHWOOD PARK & COFFEE ☕
 🌳
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Movies & Social Group - Celebrating 14 Years!\n🌳☕
  **ST. CLAIR WEST VILLAGE WALK\, WYCHWOOD PARK & COFFEE** ☕🌳\n\nHidde
 n Streets\, Storybook Homes & A Cozy Café Finish\nSome parts of Toronto f
 eel like you’ve accidentally stepped into another world.\n\nJoin us for 
 a relaxed social walk through **St. Clair West**\, leading into the quietl
 y tucked-away and exclusive **Wychwood Park** — one of the city’s most
  unique residential enclaves.\n\nWychwood Park is private\, residential\, 
 and unlike anywhere else in Toronto. The homes are all architecturally dis
 tinct — no cookie-cutter builds here — and living there involves a wai
 ting list\, a board approval process\, and community guidelines that prese
 rve its character. It feels almost village-like… peaceful\, artistic\, a
 nd slightly secret.\nThis is not a formal historical tour.\nIt’s a socia
 l walk with beautiful surroundings and good conversation.\n\n👉 **Don’
 t forget to join our WhatsApp group** – [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whats
 app.com/H59mSCbsAi018gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)\n\n***\n\n🚶‍♂️ **What W
 e’ll Do**\n\nWe’ll begin by walking west along St. Clair\, enjoying th
 e neighbourhood energy before heading into **Wychwood Park** for a gentle 
 wander through its winding streets.\n\nWe’ll begin by walking west along
  St. Clair\, enjoying the neighbourhood energy before heading into Wychwoo
 d Park for a gentle wander through its winding streets.\nAfterward\, we’
 ll make a short stop at **Artscape Wychwood Barns** to peek into the marke
 t space\, next we make a quick stop at Mr. Binz where everything starts at
  $25 and after we will head to **Bakery Garden Cafe** for a warm drink and
  time to sit\, chat\, and connect.\nSometimes the best part of the walk is
  the pause at the end. ☕\nWe’ll eventually make our way back toward St
 . Clair Subway Station.\nYou’re welcome to leave at any time.\n\n***\n\n
 ❄️ **Weather & Expectations**\n\nPlease do not sign up if you’re not
  ready to walk in real winter conditions. This event will happen in snow\,
  cold\, or typical Toronto winter weather.\n\nThe only exception: if tempe
 ratures reach -20°C\, the event will be canceled.\n\nBundle up. Dress pro
 perly. This is a winter walk.\nAlso — this is NOT a historical tour. I
 ’ll share context casually\, but the focus is social connection and enjo
 ying the neighbourhood.\n\n***\n\n🧢 Meetup Details\n📍 Meetup Locatio
 n: Outside the station by McDonald’s\n🫎 I’ll be wearing my Moose Ha
 t\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11:00 AM\nI will only wait 5 minutes.\nEarly is on tim
 e.\nOn time is late.\nWe will leave promptly\, and I won’t be able to sp
 end time trying to track people down — thank you for respecting everyone
 ’s time.\n\n***\n\n🎟️ **Meetup Fee:** $5 cash in person **or** e-tr
 ansfer to\n📧 \\*\\*[mathewmaclean@hotmail.com**](http://mathewmaclean@h
 otmail.com%2A%2A/)\nThis fee helps support the group and allows us to keep
  hosting events like this. Thank you for supporting community! 💖\n\n***
 \n\n🎒 What to Bring\n\n* Water or a warm drink\n* Good walking shoes\n*
  A small snack\n* Warm clothing (boots\, hat\, gloves — layers!)\n* Mask
  (if you prefer for indoor stops)\n\nPlease also use the washroom before a
 rriving\, as stops are limited.\n\n***\n\n📚 Learn More\nInterested in r
 eading more about Wychwood Park before we go [Click Here](https://www.thes
 tar.com/news/insight/2012/12/21/inside_the_weird_world_of_wychwood_park.ht
 ml)?\n\n🌈 Who Is This For?\nThis group is open to anyone who wants to b
 e social and make friends — whether single or not.\nWe also host:\n🎬 
 Movies\n🚶 Walks & hikes\n🎭 Arts & culture outings\n🍽️ Restauran
 t gatherings\nThere’s always something happening.\n\n***\n\nREMEMBER: Yo
 u’re welcome to just show up on the day if you’re unsure about your sc
 hedule.\nAnd as always\, sometimes plans shift and events may need to be c
 anceled — please keep an eye on updates.\n\n***\n\n👤 Organizer: Mathe
 w\nQuestions? Post on the event wall or email\n📧 torontomoviesandouting
 s@hotmail.com\n\nCome for the hidden streets. Stay for the cozy coffee.\nL
 eave feeling like you discovered a pocket of the city most people never se
 e.\nThere’s something special about wandering somewhere that feels quiet
 ly exclusive — especially when you’re not wandering alone. 🌳✨
